# Task Overview

The goal of this task is to compare text+image-to-text (vision) models side-by-side and evaluate them on factuality, instruction following, helpfulness, style, and overall preference. Your goal is to judge which response would be more acceptable to the prompt instructions about the image displayed.

First, you will review the prompt and image and try to understand what the prompt is asking for. Then, you will choose a prompt category that best suits the prompt and image. Choose 'Other' if none apply. Later, you will rate each response on 5 dimensions using the 3-point scale (Major Issue / Minor Issue / No Issue). Finally, you will compare the two responses. Decide which one handles the prompt more effectively, or select tie/I don't know if needed.

