# DO’s & DON’Ts

# QUICK START!

These DOs and DON’Ts serve as a quick-start guide to our project’s goals, helping you avoid common errors and provide the highest quality possible for your submissions!

# Do

➔ Do use the image as the Source of Truth. Verify the claims against the provided image to identify hallucinations or inaccuracies.   
Do read the text prompt to understand its intent and establish a “mental checklist” of requirements.   
➔ Do prioritize Factuality, Instruction Following, and Helpfulness over Style & Format.   
➔ Do choose the category that best describes what the prompt is asking for (e.g., Captioning, Homework, OCR, etc.). Select “Other” if none apply.

# Don’t

➔ Don’t guess on ambiguous tasks. If the prompt, image, or responses are unclear or impossible to judge, do not force a winner. Instead, select "I don't know" and use the refresh button to get a new prompt.   
➔ Don't focus only on visual appeal. While Style & Format contributes to clarity and professionalism, it should not be the main factor in your evaluation.

